name: Soul, Solitude: Who am I?
description:
“Soul, Solitude” is a series of singular object/subject in the middle of low saturated blues atmosphere. This series is my reflection to what solitude and being with yourself means.

While we’ve been raised and taught to pair up with our partner, family, friends or other person in everyday life, we sometimes feel it’s weird to be with ourselves. We often forget to connect within and make friends to the soul.

These pics were taken during my time trying to understand who I am and what I’m gonna do with my life. While navigating through all those never-ending unanswered questions, my body and emotion asked me to slow things down and experience stillness.

Photography has helped me understand stillness in its very mode so that I have some travelling archive I can look up to. It also allows me to look into who I was and who I am today. And for those reasons, this “Soul, Solitude” exists.
